<HEADLINE>
<P>
FUNDAMENTALISM AND UNREST IN INDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
India is the birthplace of four established religions: Hinduism, Buddhism, 
Sikhism and Jainism. A vast majority of Hindus in the world live there. 
</P>
<P>
So do Sikhs. So do Jains. Many Buddhists live there. And India is the second 
most Muslim-populous nation in the world. Yes, there are more Muslims in India 
than in Pakistan. 
</P>
<P>
In almost any city in India, you can find a Hindu temple, a Christian church, a 
Jain temple, a Muslim mosque and a Sikh gurdwara within a block of each other. 
Hindus, Sikhs, Jains and Buddhists intermarry and visit each other's places of 
worship. 
</P>
<P>
No nation in the world can lay claim to such an evolving diversity, to such 
distinctions. Please give India understanding. 
</P>
<P>
S. NARASIMHA REDDY, Torrance 
</P>
</TEXT>
