<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISH REPORT: ANGLERS DUEL WITH BIG CATFISH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Kazlauskas of Hemet would like nothing better than to pull a monster 
catfish out of Lake Skinner for his Thanksgiving meal. 
</P>
<P>
In October Kazlauskas, using mackerel for bait, caught cats of 23 and 27 1/2 
pounds -- the latter a lake record. Then, on Oct. 31, John Norton of Temecula, 
using shrimp, topped that at 31 3/4. 
</P>
<P>
Undaunted, Kazlauskas, fishing 70 feet deep near the dam last weekend, came 
back with one weighing 29 1/4. At last report, he and Norton were still out 
there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
