<HEADLINE>
<P>
TO BOY, 3 1/2, IRAQ IS LED BY 'SADLY INSANE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MANCHESTER, N.H. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Air Force sergeant's 3 1/2-year-old son has come up with a nickname for 
Iraqi President Saddam Hussein that has the White House laughing. 
</P>
<P>
It took Pam Averill a minute to figure out what her son, Kyle, meant when he 
said, "Sadly Insane took Daddy away." 
</P>
<P>
Kyle's father, Sgt. Kenneth Averill, was shipped from Maine to Saudi Arabia in 
August after Hussein's troops invaded Kuwait. 
</P>
<P>
"He has heard us talking and it's hard for a little kid to say 'Saddam 
Hussein,' " said Pam Averill, who is living with her parents while her husband 
is away. 
</P>
<P>
Kyle's grandmother, Joyce Austin, wrote President Bush to let him in on the 
joke. A typed reply from the White House carried the handwritten note at the 
end: "Sadly Insane? I love it." 
</P>
</TEXT>
