<P>
MAN TRAPPED UNDER HIS MOBILE HOME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRSTEN LEE SWARTZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 53-year-old Ventura man who crawled under his motor home to check on a 
suspension problem Tuesday morning was trapped beneath the vehicle and found 
unconscious there by Ventura Fire Department personnel, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Augie Luna was reported in serious condition at Ventura County Medical Center 
on Tuesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Fire personnel jacked up the motor home on Channel Heights Court and discovered 
that Luna had no pulse. They revived his heartbeat before taking him to the 
hospital about 10 a.m., department spokesman Barry Simmons said. KIRSTEN LEE 
SWARTZ 
