<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: FALLBROOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Alpine woman was killed and her husband injured when their pickup truck was 
rammed by a speeding hit-and-run driver in Fallbrook. Audry June Hall, 60, died 
at Palomar Medical Center about 5:25 p.m. Monday, a CHP spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Her husband, Sherrel Hall, 60, was in fair condition Tuesday at Scripps 
Memorial Hospital in La Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred about 3:10 p.m. Monday when the driver of a car sped 
across all four lanes of traffic at about 100 m.p.h. on southbound Interstate 
15, south of Mission Road, and struck the Halls' pickup, knocking it over an 
embankment, the CHP spokesman said. The disabled car was found about half a 
mile away. The driver had fled on foot. 
</P>
