<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of the two men charged in the only local case in which blacks have been 
charged with violating the civil rights of whites had his bail cut Tuesday from 
$10,000 to $5,000. 
</P>
<P>
Richard Maxey, 25, received the reduction in bail from Superior Court Judge 
Jesus Rodriguez. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy Dist. Atty. Luis Aragon said Maxey's wife appeared in court with the 
couple's small child, and this family support may have had some influence on 
the judge. 
</P>
<P>
Maxey is charged, along with Donnie Lee Alexander, 19, in a string of attacks 
Sept. 23 near Belmont Park in Mission Beach. Maxey and Alexander face felony 
charges of robbery and assault with a deadly weapon, as well as four 
misdemeanor counts of battery and four misdemeanor charges of civil rights 
violations. 
</P>
<P>
The pair is scheduled to go on trial Dec. 21. 
</P>
</TEXT>
