<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MAN, 56, DIES IN VAN NUYS APARTMENT FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 56-year-old man was killed Tuesday afternoon in a fire that swept through his 
Van Nuys apartment, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The name of the victim was not made public. 
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out in an apartment in the 14000 block of Delano Street at 3:06 
p.m. About 20 firefighters extinguished the blaze in 13 minutes, said Los 
Angeles City Fire Department spokesman Greg Acevedo. 
</P>
<P>
No other injuries were reported. Damage was estimated at $35,000. 
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire was under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
