<P>
AROUND THE NATION; 
</P>
<P>
TV REPORT: KRAGTHORPE TO BE FIRED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dave Kragthorpe will be fired from his job as head coach of the Oregon State 
football team, a Portland television station reported. 
</P>
<P>
KOIN-TV, citing unnamed sources close to the university administration, said 
the firing would be announced today after school Athletic Director Dutch 
Baughman meets with Kragthorpe. 
</P>
<P>
Baughman refused to comment. Oregon State went 1-10 this year. 
</P>
<P>
Kragthorpe, 57, has a 17-48-2 record at Oregon State. 
</P>
</TEXT>
