<P>
A female high school basketball player who became ill during a practice session 
collapsed and died as she was being led out of a gymnasium at Danbury, Conn. 
</P>
<P>
Her brother also died as a high school athlete. 
</P>
<P>
Patty LiVolsi, 16, a junior at Immaculate High School, collapsed in a hallway 
Monday evening moments after she told an assistant coach she was feeling 
nauseous, Coach Joseph Appello said. 
</P>
<P>
She was pronounced dead at Danbury Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
LiVolsi's older brother, Greg, died several years ago of a heart condition 
while he was in high school, said Appello. He was a football and basketball 
player. 
