<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION WATER POLO PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
NO. 8 EL TORO TO BATTLE WILSON FOR THE CHAMPIONSHIP TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
El Toro High School will try to win its third consecutive Southern Section 
water polo championship and its first in Division 4-A when it plays Long Beach 
Wilson at 8:45 tonight at Belmont Plaza in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Also played today at Belmont Plaza will be section finals in 2-A (4 p.m.) and 
3-A (5:30). 
</P>
<P>
El Toro, 25-3 and the No. 8-seeded team, won Division 3-A titles in 1988 and 
'89 before moving to 4-A this year. El Toro defeated wild-card qualifier 
Capistrano Valley, 3-2, in one semifinal. Second-seeded Wilson (22-6) defeated 
Corona del Mar, 8-4, in the other. 
</P>
<P>
Wilson is led by senior two-meter man Julian Werts and senior goalie Nick 
Fullerton. El Toro is led by senior two-meter man J.P. Mathot. 
</P>
<P>
In the Division 2-A final, second-seeded Costa Mesa (18-9) will play top-seeded 
South Pasadena (25-4). Neither team had an easy time getting to the finals: 
Costa Mesa defeated Dos Pueblos, 14-13, in overtime in one semifinal and South 
Pasadena defeated Santa Maria, 12-11, in the other. 
</P>
<P>
In Division 3-A, top-seeded Riverside Poly (23-7) will face No. 3-seeded La 
Serna (17-1). Poly defeated Miraleste, 9-6, and La Serna defeated Muir, 13-10, 
in the semifinals. ARA NAJARIAN 
</P>
