<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Teachers Honor Jones: Actor James Earl Jones received the Jean Renoir Award 
from the Los Angeles Film Teachers Assn. Monday night. Upon receiving the 
award, Jones said: "The interest of teachers in film as a means of education is 
of particular interest to me because film can be so influential in the 
education of the young. One of the things we hope to achieve with our 
production of 'Gabriel's Fire' is to bring out many of the problems faced by 
youth today. . . . Maybe if we can do a good job with this, we can help create 
a better understanding of what goes on in young people's minds, how we can help 
them and perhaps even show them how to help themselves." CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Jones 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
