<TEXT>
<P>
A previously unknown millionaire emigre who has suddenly become a contender in 
Poland's presidential race jumped ahead of Prime Minister Tadeusz Mazowiecki in 
the polls today, trailing only Lech Walesa. 
</P>
<P>
The latest survey by the government polling service showed 42-year-old 
businessman Stanislaw Tyminski was backed by 20% of respondents. 
</P>
