If no candidate wins more than 50% in Sunday's election, the top two 
vote-getters will compete in a Dec. 9 runoff. 
</P>
<P>
A pro-Mazowiecki newspaper lamented Tyminski's meteoric rise in a front-page 
commentary today: "Poland used to be the conscience of Europe, and now we have 
a chance to become the laughingstock of the world." 
