<TEXT>
<P>
Japan's Sony Corp. today posted dazzling results for the first half of its 
fiscal year, but industry analysts forecast tougher times ahead. 
</P>
<P>
Buoyed by strong sales of 8-millimeter video camcorders, audio equipment and 
color TVs, the parent company's net profits jumped 45% in the six months ended 
Sept. 30 to $307.7 million, officials said. 
